{
  "stem": "2723.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, when it got to the stage of starting secondary schooling, I sat for an entry exam into a girls' high school, which I passed with flying colors.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was really on cloud nine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So was my mother.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And a week later, we were notified-- I think that was my first realization what I was facing-- that on grounds of my Jewishness, I was refused, in spite of the fact that I had passed all their set requirements.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then there was no other schooling possible for me than that of a continuation of the same public school that I had been to, or elementary school, which set up three more classes to somehow give us a chance to continue our education.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That also came to an end in the so-called eights class, which was probably third year high school, when the Germans decreed that classes of maximum numbers-- I cannot recall how many, because we were pushing the walls out-- were still not big enough.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they put the orthodox, the Yeshiva children, and us together.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In other words, we became girls separate from boys.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the classes were enormous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the learning really was of no significance anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So actually, I finished school in '44.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I really don't think I was conscious of it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father and mother had a number of non-Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And because of my father's professional status-- he was a lawyer-- he mixed and had some very nice non-Jewish friends-- my mother even more so.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we socialized to the degree that it was known in those days to socialize with those families.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It wasn't a close relationship.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I didn't know any other.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I suppose that was the extent I accepted social interaction.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
